{
  "stem": "7238.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they said, we survived this terrible time, and now we are going to sink in this boat.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Do something.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We gave an SOS, and a little, strong boat from Scandinavia with young soldiers sent back their SOS.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We're going to save you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hold on through the night, because we cannot see.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The waves are so high, we cannot find you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Very shortly-- it was Christmas Eve-- when those guys threw lines over and pulled us out of the water, and brought us to the [INAUDIBLE] of Crete in Greece ready.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were very proud of what they did on Christmas Eve.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had all to sign a declaration to the king for the big deed, what they did.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we stood on Crete for another three weeks, waiting until they will repair the boat, and we have no food.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They didn't let us ashore because they were afraid we were sick people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We waited again.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We waited after they repaired the boat, hardly surviving, until again it started, and finally we are in Haifa.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The journey from Marseilles to Haifa takes three days, we were more than three weeks on the water.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There I discovered that finally my dream came true-- I am pregnant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The whole time when I was in Germany, I could not.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I could not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, here on this sinking boat, was a doctor from England, who understood my tragedy, my big wish to have a child, and he gave me injections.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "He saved me until we came to Haifa, and then straight to a hospital, because they put us in tents.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the first night, a big, strong wind came, and all in the air, and again we have no shelter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I remained in the hospital at this time.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
